\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The plans\", \"from\": 455, \"to\": 464}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The first-ever Summer Olympic opening ceremony not held in a stadium, the organizers are turning one of the world's most famous waterways, the River Seine, into the world's biggest theatrical stage.\", \"from\": 512, \"to\": 710, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 655, \"end\": 666, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The first-ever Summer Olympic opening ceremony\", \"from\": 512, \"to\": 558}, {\"ngram\": \"a stadium\", \"from\": 571, \"to\": 580}, {\"ngram\": \"the organizers\", \"from\": 582, \"to\": 596}, {\"ngram\": \"the world's most famous waterways\", \"from\": 616, \"to\": 649}, {\"ngram\": \"the world's biggest theatrical stage\", \"from\": 673, \"to\": 709}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead of walking into a stadium, a four-mile-long flotilla of nearly 100 boats will carry thousands of athletes from more than 200 countries past hundreds of thousands of spectators seated on the banks of the Seine.\", \"from\": 711, \"to\": 928, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 922, \"end\": 927, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4319294440380238e-15, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a stadium\", \"from\": 735, \"to\": 744}, {\"ngram\": \"a four-mile-long flotilla\", \"from\": 746, \"to\": 771}, {\"ngram\": \"nearly 100 boats\", \"from\": 775, \"to\": 791}, {\"ngram\": \"thousands\", \"from\": 803, \"to\": 812}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 816, \"to\": 824}, {\"ngram\": \"more than 200 countries\", \"from\": 830, \"to\": 853}, {\"ngram\": \"hundreds of thousands\", \"from\": 859, \"to\": 880}, {\"ngram\": \"spectators\", \"from\": 884, \"to\": 894}, {\"ngram\": \"the banks\", \"from\": 905, \"to\": 914}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The river parade will follow the course of the Seine past the iconic sites of Paris, from Austerlitz Bridge, beside the Jardin des Plantes, crossing through central Paris and finishing in front of the Trocad\\u00e9ro, where the final elements of the show and ceremony will take place.\", \"from\": 929, \"to\": 1207, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 976, \"end\": 981, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4319294440380238e-15, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 1007, \"end\": 1012, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3979478512282517e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1019, \"end\": 1036, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_d'Austerlitz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Austerlitz Bridge\", \"types\": [\"Q12280\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_d'Austerlitz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_d'Austerlitz\"}, {\"begin\": 1094, \"end\": 1099, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3979478512282517e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1130, \"end\": 1139, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trocad\\u00e9ro\", \"score\": 0.9730907954876998, \"rank\": 0.023351147168026228, \"text\": \"Trocad\\u00e9ro\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trocad\\u00e9ro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trocad\\u00e9ro\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The river parade\", \"from\": 929, \"to\": 945}, {\"ngram\": \"the course\", \"from\": 958, \"to\": 968}, {\"ngram\": \"the iconic sites\", \"from\": 987, \"to\": 1003}, {\"ngram\": \"the Jardin des Plantes\", \"from\": 1045, \"to\": 1067}, {\"ngram\": \"front\", \"from\": 1117, \"to\": 1122}, {\"ngram\": \"the final elements\", \"from\": 1147, \"to\": 1165}, {\"ngram\": \"the show\", \"from\": 1169, \"to\": 1177}, {\"ngram\": \"ceremony\", \"from\": 1182, \"to\": 1190}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 1201, \"to\": 1206}]}, {\"sentence\": \"IMAX will present NBC's live coverage of this summer's Opening Ceremony to more than 150 IMAX locations throughout the United States, providing fans with a unique and immersive theatre experience to enjoy what promises to be one of the most spectacular Opening Ceremonies in Olympic history.\", \"from\": 1209, \"to\": 1500, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1227, \"end\": 1230, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"score\": 0.7267901282463856, \"rank\": 0.36835523591058805, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\"}, {\"begin\": 1264, \"end\": 1280, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\", \"score\": 0.9999999970909812, \"rank\": 2.845343958459427e-09, \"text\": \"Opening Ceremony\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\"}, {\"begin\": 1328, \"end\": 1341, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999020528824, \"rank\": 8.085679747863828e-08, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedi